<subSubSection id="95BAEDC8B4734EBCF655C6A3399FE628" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DF0CD1307FE408BDD3110B50932FB7C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="029250FC8C3415F4937B15BBDDD38E7E" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="5204136F4DDCB7EE7416EFDEECB76858" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
(Figs 
<figureCitation id="063AA71312886296DACA5C881951E5DE" captionStart="Figures 31–32" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 31 - 32. Platensina platyptera Hendel 31 habitus (dorsal) 32 habitus (lateral)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures31-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669204" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">31</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DFE3A2DEFEFBB712FD4AC73F2A02F5D0" captionStart="Figures 31–32" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figures 31 - 32. Platensina platyptera Hendel 31 habitus (dorsal) 32 habitus (lateral)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures31-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669204" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">32</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
This species was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation id="A470D54D6459FA77210DD88A83D25ECF" author="Hendel, F" journalOrPublisher="Annales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="424 - 467" refId="B14" refString="Hendel, F, 1915. H. Sauter's Formosa-Ausbeute. Tephritinae. Annales Musei Nationalis Hungarici 13: 424 - 467" title="H. Sauter's Formosa-Ausbeute. Tephritinae." volume="13" year="1915">Hendel (1915)</bibRefCitation>
from Taiwan. It was recorded from India by 
<bibRefCitation id="3BE0FACFBA8C3C979A3F0B07D69B2C46" author="Hancock, DL" journalOrPublisher="Australian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="305 - 320" refId="B9" refString="Hancock, DL, 2012. Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya. Australian Entomologist 39 (4): 305 - 320" title="Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya." volume="39" year="2012">Hancock (2012)</bibRefCitation>
, based on photographs by the senior author. It is a medium-sized species with broad quadrate hyaline markings in cells c and r1, round hyaline spots along the wing margin and in almost all the cells. It is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1B59B77939FFCB2BC4978976BCAB8B83" class="Insecta" genus="P." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="P. zodiacalis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zodiacalis">
<emphasis id="5F475E1ECAB7F7554E1EEC24443C9C2F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">P. zodiacalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bezzi) but can be differentiated by the presence of apical scutellar setae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="0A6D554F1B88C383C384ED1B5B6A6E0F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures31-32" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669204" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figures 31–32" startId="F8">
<paragraph id="D8029061312866DBF2D1B3D3BBAC9CC4" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<emphasis id="B03F96342C3CEF0EEA9B5E89565F8779" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Figures 31-32.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="045F0B8B6243A37D86A34B06BD4F655B" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Platensina" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platensina platyptera" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="platyptera">
<emphasis id="0F11587FBB4D1BCDA857A76614FCB636" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Platensina platyptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hendel 
<emphasis id="C0490FE4C61A3B156C95EC3768F86A84" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">31</emphasis>
habitus (dorsal) 
<emphasis id="CE4DC06418EA8AAC04618147830BE99B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">32</emphasis>
habitus (lateral).
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4AD3E2FD8EB86FE94BDE3A87E914A0C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="male genitalia">
<paragraph id="0614FE035B6E516C9911F06F7F2F551B" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Male genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D80D991133BDB05B8D0012C83DEB1A68" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Epandrium (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="4BE1AEB129B178AF72ADE639F7DD6FE7" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">33</figureCitation>
) dark brown, heavily sclerotised, with no demarcation from lateral surstylus (in profile view); epandrium and surstyli oval in posterior view, with well developed prensisetae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0BC2DCF337273BC943F6509CDBBD5AD6" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">34</figureCitation>
). Phallus elongate (1.54 mm long including glans); glans stout, with broad sclerotised rod (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BFE28829C7B2A25783523748621F68DD" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">35</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="F2816A15231A9D52DFC97A9EE1AF3F2F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figures 33–41" startId="F9">
