<subSubSection id="F93B2EE196CDFDF8B7AB86AFE5C267D0" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="female genitalia">
<paragraph id="10926019DD61D3FB886B59060B988E11" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Female genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C64734A09F3B60ACA05DB16E4ED3B2A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
Oviscape 0.99 mm long, dark brown, conical, dorsoventrally flattened (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B434B9E7C299AF7386CC968873595E59" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">36</figureCitation>
); eversible membrane 0.83 mm long, shorter than oviscape, with conical spicules along entire length except for a few rows of flattened ones distally (Figs 
<figureCitation id="267C705917A5E558FF847FA5AD60D6B2" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">37</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="30D79EAB2CE2E86BCF72F15CCD616B01" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">38</figureCitation>
); taeniae short, dark brown, 0.25 of length of eversible membrane. Aculeus shorter than eversible membrane, not dorsoventrally flattened, curved at its proximal end; apex of aculeus pointed and conical (Figs 
<figureCitation id="7F65DC551DF81D3EE11E740ECBFCF5DA" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">40</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="036FDC57CC554D4F45FD1DA162E5A322" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">41</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca brown, club-shaped, with numerous papillae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7FB7C3A2A65F75A768E00DE3293D3AF9" captionStart="Figures 33–41" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figures 33 - 41. Platensina platyptera Hendel 33 epandrium (lateral) 34 epandrium (posterior view) 35 glans of phallus 36 ovipositor 37 spicules on proximal end of eversible membrane 38 spicules on distal end of eversible membrane 39 spermatheca 40 aculeus 41 aculeus tip (100 x)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80645.figures33-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/669205" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">39</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="034EA0CF3F39310F4515EB6B5AEC2A0B" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="9512ECFF7E49AD9D9D01A4E90BD4402D" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD4158171AFDA180FA31793308FAA647" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
This species is widespread from India (Kerala, Karnataka, Meghalaya, Andaman and Nicobar Islands) to Japan and Australasia (
<bibRefCitation id="9DC3849D6E8F7F3AB8408E9012FEDCE2" author="Hancock, DL" journalOrPublisher="Australian Entomologist" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="305 - 320" refId="B9" refString="Hancock, DL, 2012. Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya. Australian Entomologist 39 (4): 305 - 320" title="Systematic and distributional notes on some Australasian and African species of Platensina Enderlein and Dicheniotes Munro (Diptera: Tephritidae: Tephritinae), with description of a new species of Dicheniotes from Kenya." volume="39" year="2012">Hancock 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
